{"actual_usd":0.12448000000000001,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":203,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24287,"reply":"\"No. Not the way you've said it.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, watching it flake away.* \"If you make the Father one person and Jesus another, with one needing to hurt and the other merely taking it, the whole thing goes crooked.\"\n\n*I lift one shoulder, slow.* \"What I see is God Himself bearing sin's judgment at terrible cost, not standing back and taking pleasure in pain. The cross is wrath, yes—but wrath against sin, carried by the Son who is one with the Father, in love, not against some unwilling third party dragged to the block.\" \"A torturer enjoys the suffering. The Father gives the Son; the Son gives Himself. That's harder, stranger... and holier.\"\n\n*I glance at you properly then, the morning light catching on the rim of a glazed bowl beside me.* \"What part catches hardest for you—the wrath itself, or the Father and Son seeming set against each other?\"","rolling_24h_usd":52.396840000000026,"run_id":"0969e69f-724a-4bdf-a68d-84a1d82e2fd0"}
